2. incesto stupro: Cicero represents the act of Clodius as a duplex crimen, incesto referring to the Bona Dea,and stupro to Pompeia. Cf. Dig. 48. 18. 5. He contiuually calls the offence of Clodius stuprum, e. g. Har. Resp. 33, 38, 44. The conjecture of Rau, who, from the Schol. Bob, would read incestu, end cut out stupro as a gloss, is attractive, since incestu would exactly balance interitu. 3. iudicium decern: for the facts see Art. i. 16. The senate had wished the jurors to be selected by the praetor, but under the lex Fufia, which was actually carried, they were chosen by seruitio in the usual manner.
